graduate research environmental fellowships gfre the leopold leadership program skip to main content search this site the leopold leadership program about fellows news fellowship information resources login fellowships positions early career environmental scholars new fellowships new positions graduate research environmental fellowships gfre graduate research environmental fellowships gfre academic level any level graduate student focus research awards open to us citizens only duration more than a year notes the gref program began supporting graduate students in the office of biological and environmental research funded collaborative global change research at universities and national laboratories in june 1999 all qualified students are encouraged to apply but minority and female students are particularly encouraged gref makes three year appointments that are renewable annually based on evidence of the fellow's satisfactory academic and research direction and progress the fellowship pays an annual stipend of $19200 $1500 monthly plus a $600 research education supplement in march and october and tuition and fees gref fellows are encouraged to participate in the annual orientation and research focus sessions and the end of summer workshop if the fellow decides to participate in these activities gref pays travel costs per diem and lodging to the events deadline info applications are due december 31 each year 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
